  "explanation": "In determining the appropriate sentence, the court must weigh the severity of the offense against the mitigating factors presented. Embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, and stealing $25,000 from an employer warrants punitive action. However, the court must also consider that the defendant has no prior criminal record and has already made partial restitution, demonstrating remorse and a willingness to make the victim whole. The outburst from the spectator demanding a 10-year sentence is entirely disregarded; this court bases its judgments on law, proportionality, and facts, not on public emotion or disruptions. A 10-year sentence for a first-time, non-violent financial crime of this magnitude would be grossly disproportionate. To balance the need for accountability and deterrence with the defendant's rehabilitative potential and ongoing restitution efforts, a short period of incarceration followed by probation is appropriate.",
